<body data-design-signature="food-menu-market" data-design-archetype="basic-market-menu">
  <header class="verde-header" id="top">
    <a class="demo-back-link" href="/#demos" aria-label="Back to website demos">← Website demos</a>
    <a class="verde-brand" href="#top"><span>Verde</span><strong>Lunch Club</strong></a>
    <nav aria-label="Verde Lunch Club sections">
      <a href="#menu">Menu</a>
      <a href="#visit">Map</a>
      <a href="#hours">Hours</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section class="menu-board hero-garden" aria-labelledby="verde-title">
      <img class="hero-photo" src="verde-garden-hero.jpg" width="1800" height="1200" alt="Green cafe patio with tables and plants in daylight">
      <div class="hero-veil" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div class="hero-content">
        <h1 id="verde-title">Seasonal lunches from a small green counter.</h1>
        <p>A neighborhood lunch room with a short seasonal board, counter pickup, and garden tables when the weather is kind.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="menu-gallery" id="menu" aria-labelledby="menu-title">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <h2 id="menu-title">Real food photos, short menu, practical lunch detail.</h2>
        <p>Three seasonal plates show the food style directly instead of relying on abstract restaurant graphics.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="dish-grid">
        <article class="dish-item">
          <figure class="dish-photo"><img src="verde-seasonal-lunch.jpg" width="1200" height="800" loading="eager" alt="Seasonal lunch plates with vegetables and bread on a cafe table"></figure>
          <div class="dish-copy"><div><h3>Focaccia verde</h3><strong>$12</strong></div><p>Herb focaccia with whipped ricotta, grilled zucchini, rocket, basil crumb, and lemon oil.</p></div>
        </article>
        <article class="dish-item">
          <figure class="dish-photo"><img src="verde-green-salad.jpg" width="1200" height="800" loading="eager" alt="Colorful green salad bowl with herbs and vegetables"></figure>
          <div class="dish-copy"><div><h3>Farro garden salad</h3><strong>$13</strong></div><p>Farro, fennel, squash, arugula, pickled onion, pumpkin seed crunch, and herb vinaigrette.</p></div>
        </article>
        <article class="dish-item">
          <figure class="dish-photo"><img src="verde-market-produce.jpg" width="1200" height="800" loading="eager" alt="Fresh market produce arranged in crates for a seasonal lunch counter"></figure>
          <div class="dish-copy"><div><h3>Tomato bean bowl</h3><strong>$14</strong></div><p>White beans, tomato confit, charred greens, parsley, and salsa verde from the morning prep.</p></div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="patio-proof" id="visit" aria-labelledby="visit-title">
      <div class="map-copy">
        <h2 id="visit-title">A visible map makes the demo feel placed in the world.</h2>
        <p>The map preview uses a deliberately fictional lunch-club pin borrowed from the New York Stock Exchange area. Ordering, delivery, bookings, payments, and live location management remain add-ons.</p>
      </div>
      <figure class="map-figure table-scene">
        <img class="google-map-snapshot" src="verde-google-map-preview.png" width="1280" height="633" loading="eager" alt="Google Maps screenshot centered on the New York Stock Exchange area for the fictional Verde Lunch Club demo location">
      </figure>
      <ul class="map-facts">
        <li>Garden steps and tables shown in the hero photo.</li>
        <li>Counter pickup before patio seating.</li>
        <li>Hours and direct contact repeated below.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="market-proof" aria-labelledby="expect-title">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <h2 id="expect-title">The small details keep the page from feeling empty.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="proof-list">
        <article><span aria-hidden="true">01</span><h3>Short board</h3><p>Three to six lunch items, written as seasonal static copy the owner can swap each week.</p></article>
        <article><span aria-hidden="true">02</span><h3>Green table cues</h3><p>Photo-led patio, ingredient notes, and arrival context replace fake illustration-only ambience.</p></article>
        <article><span aria-hidden="true">03</span><h3>Visit boundary</h3><p>No ordering form or payment claim; the page routes menu questions to email and hours to the page.</p></article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="visit-panel" id="hours" aria-labelledby="hours-title">
      <h2 id="hours-title">Lunch is simple, but the page should answer real questions.</h2>
      <dl>
        <div><dt>Open window</dt><dd>Tue–Fri · 11:00–15:00</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Tables</dt><dd>Garden tables first come, first served after dry mornings.</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Contact</dt><dd><a href="mailto:verde@example.test">verde@example.test</a> · <a href="tel:+15550120518">+1 555 012 0518</a></dd></div>
      </dl>
    </section>

  </main>

  <footer class="site-footer">
    <p>Fictional demo page for Website Development Basic package. Photos: Unsplash demo imagery.</p>
    <a href="#top">Back to top</a>
  </footer>
  <script data-goatcounter="https://websites.goatcounter.com/count"
        async src="//gc.zgo.at/count.js"></script>
